y=np.zeros((data.shape[0],HEIGHT_CELLS,WIDTH_CELLS),dtype=np.float32)           #seperating the image and masks
X=np.zeros((data.shape[0],IMAGE_SIZE,IMAGE_SIZE,3),dtype=np.float32)
preprocess_input_img=get_preprocessing(BACKBONE)

for index in range(data.shape[0]):
  img=data[index][0]
  img = cv2.resize(img, dsize=(IMAGE_SIZE,IMAGE_SIZE), interpolation=cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
  try:
    img=img[:,:,:3]
  except:
    continue
  X[index]=preprocess_input_img(np.array(img,dtype=np.float32))

  for i in data[index][1]:
    x1 = int(i['points'][0]['x'] * 28)
    x1 = int(i["points"][0]['x'] * 28)
    x2 = int(i["points"][1]['x'] * 28)
    y1 = int(i["points"][0]['y'] * 28)
    y2 = int(i["points"][1]['y'] * 28)
    y[index][x1:x2,y1:y2]=1

In [ ]:
base_model=Unet(backbone_name='resnet34',encoder_weights='imagenet')             #modelling the architecture
input_base_model = Input(shape=(IMAGE_SIZE,IMAGE_SIZE,3))

layer1=Conv2D(3,(1,1))(input_base_model)
layer2=base_model(layer1)

x1 = Conv2D(10, kernel_size =3,strides=2,padding = "same", activation="relu")(layer2)
x2= Conv2D(10, kernel_size=3,strides=2,padding = "same", activation="relu")(x1)
x3 = Conv2D(10, kernel_size=3,strides=2,padding = "same", activation="relu")(x2)
x4 = Conv2D(1, kernel_size=2,strides=2,padding = "same", activation="relu")(x3)

x5=UpSampling2D()(x4)
model = Model(input_base_model, x5, name=base_model.name)

In [ ]:
def dice_coefficient(y_true,y_pred):           #Defining the dice coefficient
  numerator = 2*tf.reduce_sum(y_true*y_pred)
  denominator= tf.reduce_sum(y_true+y_pred)
  return numerator/(denominator+tf.keras.backend.epsilon())
In [ ]:
def loss_funct(y_true, y_pred):        #Defining the loss function
  return binary_crossentropy(y_true, y_pred) - tf.math.log(dice_coefficient(y_true, y_pred) + tf.keras.backend.epsilon())
In [ ]:
model.compile(optimizer='Adam',loss=loss_funct,metrics=[dice_coefficient])

class IdentityMetadata():                        #creating a class for storing metadata of each image
  def __init__(self,base,name,file):
    self.base=base
    self.name=name
    self.file=file
  def __repr__(self):
    return self.image_path()
  def image_path(self):
    return os.path.join(self.base,self.name,self.file)

def load_metadata(new_path):
  metadata=[]
  for i in os.listdir(new_path):
    for f in os.listdir(os.path.join(new_path, i)):
      ext = os.path.splitext(f)[1]
      if ext == '.jpg' or ext == '.jpeg':
        metadata.append(IdentityMetadata(new_path, i, f))
  return np.array(metadata)

metadata = load_metadata(new_path)

def load_image(path):

    return img[...,::-1]

from keras.models import Sequential                 #the architecture
from keras.layers import ZeroPadding2D, Convolution2D, MaxPooling2D, Dropout, Flatten, Activation

def vgg_face():
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1),input_shape=(224,224, 3)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))

    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))

    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))

    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))

    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))

    model.add(Convolution2D(4096, (7, 7), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Convolution2D(4096, (1, 1), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Convolution2D(2622, (1, 1)))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Activation('softmax'))
    return model

a = metadata.shape[0]                                 #loading images and generatin the embeddings
embeddings = np.zeros((a,2622))
for i in range (a):
  img_path=metadata[i].image_path()
  img = load_image(img_path)

  img=(img/255).astype(np.float32)
  img=cv2.resize(img,dsize = (224,224))

  embeddings[i]=vgg_face_descriptor.predict(np.expand_dims(img,axis=0))[0]

def distance(emb1, emb2):           #calculating the distance between the vectors
    return np.sum(np.square(emb1 - emb2))
In [62]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt           #function to plot the image and distance

def show_pair(idx1, idx2):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,3))
    plt.suptitle(f'Distance = {distance(embeddings[idx1], embeddings[idx2]):.2f}')
    plt.subplot(121)
    plt.imshow(load_image(metadata[idx1].image_path()))
    plt.subplot(122)
    plt.imshow(load_image(metadata[idx2].image_path()));

show_pair(7, 5)
show_pair(9, 320)

from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder

targets = np.array([m.name for m in metadata])             #encoding the labels
encoder = LabelEncoder()
encoder.fit(targets)

y = encoder.transform(targets)

train_idx = np.arange(metadata.shape[0]) % 9 != 0         #splitting the data into train and test set
test_idx = np.arange(metadata.shape[0]) % 9 == 0

X_train = embeddings[train_idx] #train examples
X_test = embeddings[test_idx] #test examples

y_train = y[train_idx]
y_test = y[test_idx]

print("X_train:", X_train.shape[0])
print("X_test:", X_test.shape[0])
print("y_train:", y_train.shape[0])
print("y_train:", y_test.shape[0])

X_train: 9573
X_test: 1197
y_train: 9573
y_train: 1197

In [57]:
from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier               #training an SVM and KNN model
knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=1, metric='euclidean')
svc = LinearSVC()

knn.fit(X_train, y_train)
svc.fit(X_train, y_train)

acc_knn = accuracy_score(y_test, knn.predict(X_test))
acc_svc = accuracy_score(y_test, svc.predict(X_test))

print(f'KNN accuracy = {acc_knn}, SVM accuracy = {acc_svc}')

KNN accuracy = 0.9197994987468672, SVM accuracy = 0.9615705931495405
